To create a smooth game and use images for animations, you might consider using a game development library or framework that supports C, such as SDL or SFML. However, these libraries are more complex and require a good understanding of game development concepts.

If you want to stick with C and the curses library, you can create a text-based snake game, but it won't have the smooth animations or image support that you're looking for.

